        contents_html_en: `<img src="../blog-image-18.png" alt="Potato Pancakes" class="blog-post-image"><h2>Potato Pancakes â€“ A Dish That Elevates the Ingredientâ€™s Natural Flavor</h2><p>The key to this recipe is crisping each piece to perfection. A dish made purely from the natural flavor of potatoes. Crunchy on the outside, tender on the insideâ€”let me introduce you to potato pancakes.</p><h3>ğŸ›’ Ingredients (Makes 2â€“3 pancakes)</h3><ul><li>2â€“3 medium potatoes</li><li>A pinch of salt</li><li>2â€“3 tbsp cooking oil</li><li>(Optional) 1â€“2 tbsp flour or pancake mix</li><li>(Optional) Â¼ onion, chopped chili pepper â€“ to enhance the flavor</li></ul><h3>ğŸ”ª Preparation</h3><p>Peel and grate the potatoes using a grater or blender â†’ If using a blender, add a little water to help blend smoothly.</p><p>Place the grated potatoes in a strainer or cloth and squeeze out the excess liquid â†’ Let the squeezed liquid sit; once the starch settles, discard the top water and mix the starch back into the potato batter for extra crispiness.</p><p>Add onion, chili, or flour if desiredâ€”but avoid adding too much, so the potatoâ€™s natural flavor doesnâ€™t get overpowered.</p><h3>ğŸ³ Cooking Method</h3><ol><li>Mix the grated potato with salt and settled starch.</li><li>Preheat a pan over medium heat, add plenty of oil, and spread the batter thinly.</li><li>Cook until golden brown on one side, then flip and crisp the other.</li><li>Place on paper towels to absorb excess oil, and serve.</li></ol><h3>ğŸ¥£ Dipping Sauce</h3><p>Serve with a refreshing soy dipping sauce:</p><ul><li>2 tbsp soy sauce</li><li>1 tbsp vinegar</li><li>1 tbsp water</li><li>A pinch of sugar (optional)</li><li>Chopped green onion or chili (optional)</li></ul><p>Mix well and enjoy the tangy balance with the mild potato flavor!</p><h3>âš ï¸ Cooking Caution</h3><p>Potato pancakes involve hot oil, so take care while cooking â†’ When spreading batter, do it gently and keep hands away from splashing oil â†’ If the batter is too moist or the oil is overheated, it may splatterâ€”cook on medium heat for safety.</p><h3>ğŸ’¡ Tips</h3><ul><li>Generous oil helps achieve a crispy outer layer.</li><li>You can keep the skin on for a rustic textureâ€”just wash well.</li><li>Add cheese, bacon, or scallions to create flavorful twists.</li></ul><p>A slightly unconventional way to eat potatoes? Try it and you might just change your mind.</p>`
