        contents_html_en: `<img src="../blog-image-19.png" alt="Clam Chowder" class="blog-post-image"><h2>Clam Chowder â€“ The Flavor of Soft Cream Embracing the Sea</h2><p>A rich sea flavor wrapped in smooth cream. Potatoes, bacon, clams, and a deeply flavorful cream sauce. A dish where aroma and taste harmonize beautifully. Clam chowder. Today, we invite you to experience the taste of the cream tide.</p><h3>ğŸ›’ Ingredients (Serves 2â€“3)</h3><ul><li>Clam meat â€“ 150g (canned or fresh)</li><li>Potato â€“ 1</li><li>Onion â€“ Â½</li><li>Bacon â€“ 2 strips</li><li>Milk â€“ 1 cup</li><li>Heavy cream â€“ Â½ cup</li><li>Flour â€“ 1 tbsp</li><li>Butter â€“ 1 tbsp</li><li>Water or stock â€“ 1 cup</li><li>Salt, pepper</li><li>(Optional) Celery, thyme, parsley</li></ul><h3>ğŸ”ª Preparation</h3><p>Peel and dice potato into 1.5cm cubes</p><p>Finely chop onion; thinly slice celery if using</p><p>Cut bacon into small cubes</p><p>For canned clams: set aside liquid for later use</p><p>For fresh clams: rinse well, soak in salted water to remove sand, briefly boil, then remove shells</p><h3>âš ï¸ Notes for Cooking Seafood</h3><p>When using fresh clams, make sure to soak them for sand removal, then boil and shell them before cooking.</p><p>Add clam meat at the end of cookingâ€”boiling them too long makes them chewy.</p><p>For sensitive stomachs or safer handling, canned clams are a reliable option.</p><h3>ğŸ³ How to Make</h3><ol><li>Melt butter in a pot and sautÃ© bacon until golden.</li><li>Add onion, potato, and celery and stir-fry for 2â€“3 minutes.</li><li>Add flour and mix well, then slowly pour in water or stock while stirring to prevent lumps.</li><li>Simmer for 10 minutes until potatoes are tender.</li><li>Add clam meat, milk, and heavy cream, then simmer over low heat for 5â€“7 minutes.</li><li>Season with salt, pepper, and herbs to taste.</li><li>Adjust thickness with a bit more milk or stock if desired.</li><li>Serve in a bowl and garnish with parsley.</li></ol><h3>ğŸ’¡ Tips</h3><ul><li>Canned clam juice can deepen the broth's flavorâ€”add a spoonful to taste.</li><li>A dash of nutmeg gives it an elegant aroma.</li><li>Best served with crusty bread like sourdough or baguette.</li><li>Cut potatoes large enough to hold shape while cooking.</li></ul><p>Let creamy waves bring you the warmth and depth of the seaâ€”today's clam chowder awaits.</p>`
