        contents_html_en: `<img src="../blog-image-20.png" alt="Cheese Spaghetti" class="blog-post-image"><h2>Cheese Spaghetti â€“ Failproof Flavor from the Oven</h2><p>This dish is remembered by its familiar appearance. And with that familiarity, it offers a comforting taste we know and love. Golden baked top and bright, tangy sauceâ€”cheese spaghetti at its most inviting. Let the oven take care of dinner tonight.</p><h3>ğŸ›’ Ingredients (Serves 2)</h3><ul><li>Spaghetti â€“ 160â€“180g</li><li>Tomato sauce â€“ 1 cup</li><li>Mozzarella cheese â€“ 80â€“100g</li><li>Grated Parmesan cheese â€“ 2 tbsp</li><li>Minced garlic â€“ 1 tsp</li><li>Onion â€“ Â¼ (finely chopped)</li><li>Bacon or ham â€“ 50g (optional)</li><li>Olive oil â€“ 1 tbsp</li><li>Salt & pepper â€“ to taste</li><li>Fresh basil or parsley â€“ optional</li><li>Oven-safe baking dish or pan</li></ul><h3>ğŸ”ª Preparation</h3><p>Boil spaghetti in salted water for 8â€“10 minutes until al dente, then drain.</p><p>Chop garlic, onion, and bacon, then sautÃ© lightly in olive oil.</p><p>Preheat oven to 180Â°C (350Â°F).</p><h3>ğŸ³ How to Make</h3><ol><li>In a mixing bowl, combine cooked pasta with sautÃ©ed ingredients and tomato sauce.</li><li>Season with salt and pepper and toss well.</li><li>Transfer to a baking dish and top generously with mozzarella and Parmesan.</li><li>Bake in the preheated oven for 15â€“20 minutes until cheese is melted and golden.</li><li>Garnish with fresh basil or parsley if desired.</li></ol><h3>âš ï¸ Caution</h3><p>Check mid-bake to prevent cheese from burning.</p><p>Be careful with hot ovenwareâ€”use mitts to avoid burns.</p><p>If using lots of cheese, ensure the dish has enough depth to prevent overflow.</p><h3>ğŸ’¡ íŒ</h3><ul><li>Homemade tomato sauce adds depth: sautÃ© crushed tomatoes with garlic and onion.</li><li>Try mixing cheesesâ€”cheddar, gouda, or blue cheese add personality.</li><li>No oven? Use an air fryer with an oven-safe dish at 160â€“170Â°C for 15 minutes.</li><li>Leftovers make a great next-day tomato risotto-style dish when reheated in a pan.</li></ul><p>We know this flavor well. Now cook it your way.</p>`
