        contents_html_en: `<img src="../blog-image-21.png" alt="Chicken Salad" class="blog-post-image"><h2>Chicken Salad â€“ A Meal for Your Body's Well-being</h2><p>There are ingredients we know are good for us, but arenâ€™t always easy to get used to. But what if they were paired with a rich and flavorful dressing? Chicken breast and a variety of fresh vegetables. Let this balanced, dressing-crafted dish be your next nutritious meal.</p><h3>ğŸ›’ Ingredients (Serves 2)</h3><ul><li>1â€“2 chicken breasts</li><li>Romaine or iceberg lettuce</li><li>Cherry tomatoes</li><li>Cucumber</li><li>Boiled egg</li><li>Avocado (optional)</li><li>Olive oil</li><li>Balsamic vinegar or lemon juice</li><li>Salt and pepper</li><li>Nuts (almonds, walnuts, etc., optional)</li></ul><h3>ğŸ”ª Preparation</h3><p>Chicken breast: Season with salt and pepper, cook in a pan or air fryer, let cool, then slice</p><p>Vegetables: Wash thoroughly and cut into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cherry tomatoes: Halve</p><p>Cucumber: Slice thinly</p><p>Boiled egg: Quarter after cooling</p><p>Avocado: Remove pit and peel, slice thinly</p><p>Nuts: Lightly toast in a pan or use raw</p><h3>ğŸ¥£ How to Make</h3><ol><li>In a large bowl, add all the prepared vegetables.</li><li>Top with chicken breast, avocado, egg, tomatoes, and nuts.</li><li>Mix olive oil, balsamic vinegar or lemon juice, salt, and pepper to make the dressing.</li><li>Drizzle over the salad and toss lightly or serve as is.</li></ol><h3>âš ï¸ Notes</h3><p>Ingredients like nuts, eggs, avocado, and dressing components may affect those with allergies or sensitive digestion.</p><p>Finding the right healthful ingredients for your own body is important.</p><p>If trying something new, be sure to check ingredient labels or consult dietary guidance.</p><h3>ğŸ’¡ Tips</h3><ul><li>Add a spoonful of plain yogurt to the dressing for a creamier taste.</li><li>You can swap the chicken breast with smoked or boiled chicken thigh.</li><li>Adding chickpeas, lentils, or quinoa creates a more filling, complete meal.</li><li>Leftovers work wonderfully in a wrap or sandwich.</li></ul>`
